<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36218c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36218c">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36218c"> 218(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ponies</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Mormonism.]</font> <font color="green">[The angel Moroni speaks to Joseph Smith of a book &ldquo;written on gold plates&rdquo; (the Book of Mormon).]</font> Moroni also spake unto him saying that there were likewise &hellip; two media with the tablets &hellip; which would enable Joseph to translate the tablets without difficulty. He was further <font color="green">[prudently]</font> instructed by Moroni that if he dared show either the plates or <mark>the ponies</mark> to any one he would be destroyed. <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 370</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
